<module>
    <h>gille</h>
    <p><g>gille</g>
        <en>a boy</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
        noun</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>adjectives</h>
        <module id="beag">
            <h>beag</h>
            <p><g>gille <a href="?gd=beag">beag</a></g>
                <en>a little boy</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Càit a bheil an gille beag an diugh?</gd>
                        <tr>Where is the little boy today?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an gille beag anns an sgoil? Chan eil.</gd>
                        <tr>Is the little boy in the school? No, he isn’t.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Có tha anns a’ chraoibh? Tha an gille beag.</gd>
                        <tr>Who is in the tree? The little boy is.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 40</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
        <module id="moor">
            <h>mór</h>
            <p><g>gille <a href="?gd=moor">mór</a></g>
                <en>a big boy</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an gille mór.</gd>
                        <tr>The boy is big.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
        <module id="ceaarr">
            <h>ceàrr</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=ceaarr">ceàrr</a> air gille</g>
                <en>wrong with a boy</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dé tha ceàrr air a’ ghille seo? Tha a cheann goirt.</gd>
                        <tr>What is wrong with this boy? His head is sore.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>prepositions</h>
        <module id="dorus">
            <h>dorus</h>
            <p><g>gille aig <a href="?gd=dorus">dorus</a></g>
                <en>a boy at a door</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha robh an gille aig an dorus.</gd>
                        <tr>The boy was not at the door.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <module id="sgoil">
            <h>sgoil</h>
            <p><g>gille ann an <a href="?gd=sgoil">sgoil</a></g>
                <en>a boy in a school</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an gille beag anns an sgoil? Chan eil.</gd>
                        <tr>Is the little boy in the school? No, he isn’t.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <!-- <section>
            <h>subject</h>-->
        <module id="cluich">
            <h>cluich</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=cluich">cluich</a> gille</g>
                <en>a boy plays</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an gille a’ cluich? Tha,</gd>
                        <tr>Is the boy playing? Yes, he is.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
        <!--</section>-->
    </section>

